title: For Sale/Trade:  Portable solar array- backup power station, survival electricity
postcontent:
Up for sale is my solar array. I made it out of a packaged solar panel kit that came with the charge controller, and I added two 35 ah (amp hour) deep cycle batteries and ran them in parallel to make it a 12v 70 ah system. I had the box, which was originally a planter box, and I converted it to house the system.   I bought the 45w solar kit from harbor freight about two months ago for about $180, and I have had the batteries longer, I think I paid $70 each a while back. 

This system is very portable but heavy. If you separate it from the box, it is very easy to take camping or whatever to have lights and if you use an inverter like you plug into your cars cigarette lighter, you can run small appliances and charge cell phones, etc.  The way it is mounted on the box, I have it hinged so you can change the angle of the panels through the day, and turn the box (which is on casters) to follow the sun for maximum charge. It would also be great as a small backup or emergency power source for your house.

title: For Sale:  NIB Ruger 10-22 Stainless steel barrel/Synthetic Stock
postcontent:
Very hard to find model, with its stainless steel barrel and synthetic black all weather stock.  The Ruger 10-22 is thought by many to be one of the best .22 rifles made and a top choice for small game hunting, survival, training and more. The PT1911 differs from its many competitors in the 1911-style market in that the basic model offers a package of features found on top-end models from more expensive semi-custom pistol manufacturers such as Springfield Armory, Para-Ordnance, and Kimber Manufacturing at a significantly lower cost.

Featuring a forged steel frame, the standard PT1911 is hand-fit in the Taurus factory and includes popular combat and competition custom features such as a "Beavertail" grip safety with memory groove, extended ambidextrous thumb safety and slide stop controls, lowered and flared ejection port, frame checkering, and other niceties unusual for a pistol of its price range.
